        <name>write_elapsed_time</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_ets_cb::write_elapsed_time</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Write elapsed time callback (OPTIONAL). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Called when a BLE client writes to the Current Elapsed Time characteristic. Only applicable if <simplesect kind="attention"><para>Available only when the following Kconfig option is enabled: <computeroutput>CONFIG_BT_ETS_CURRENT_ELAPSED_TIME_WRITABLE</computeroutput>. is enabled. Application should validate time source quality, range, and other constraints.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Clock Status and Clock Capabilities are excluded from writes per spec.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>time</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Elapsed time structure written by client.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Result code indicating acceptance or specific rejection reason. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
